cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about multi-label image classification using deep convolutional neural networks and recurrent neural networks. The paper focuses on addressing the challenge of predicting small objects and visual concepts in multi-label image classification. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model that characterizes the latent semantic dependencies at the regional level, which involves the use of recurrent neural networks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on several benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
